Malice:

He smiled to her explaination, spending one on one time was always good.  He was stopped in mid thought when she leaned in and planted a kiss on his cheek.  She apologized, but there was no need, other than she could not totally commit herself to loving him.  He placed his hands on her shoulders, his own spark a bit unsteady.  He leaned in and kissed her lips lightly, his faceplates trying to articulate it correctly for her.

&quot;Nothing to apologize for.  It&#39;s okay, I like speading time alone with you too.  I know I should between you two, but I&#39;m not sure it would be such a great idea.  But please don&#39;t fight with her, don&#39;t fight about me, it would hurt me deeply.  Maybe I can sort things out and make a choice, but for now, let&#39;s just worry about work space romance, hm?&quot; he ended with a wink and a slight smile.

But he did mean it, if they forced him to choose... it might end badly for all of them.

